{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Look, I've seen all this with my own eyes, and heard it with my own ears, and I understand it.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I know what you know. You're no better than me.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But I would still like to speak to the Almighty: I want to prove myself to God!\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "As for you, you cover things up[^70] by telling lies! You are all like doctors who can't heal anyone!\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I wish you would all be quiet! That would be the wisest thing for you to do.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Listen to my argument and pay attention to what I have to say.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do you think you can tell lies to defend God? Are you talking deceitfully on his behalf?\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Or are you wanting to show God favoritism? Are you going to argue God's case for him?\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Will you be found to be doing good when God examines you? Can you fool him as if he's a human being?\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "No, he will definitely rebuke you if you secretly show him favoritism!\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Isn't his majesty terrifying to you? Aren't you so afraid of him you're paralyzed?\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Your sayings are as helpful as ashes; your arguments as weak as clay.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Be quiet. Don't talk to me. Let me speak, come what may.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I take responsibility for myself; I am ready to risk my life.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Even though he kills me, I will hope in him. [^71] I am still going to defend my ways before him.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "By doing this I will be saved since no godless person could come before him.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Listen carefully to what I say, pay attention to my explanation.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Look, I've prepared my case—I know I will be proved right.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who wants to argue with me? If I'm proved wrong, I'm prepared to be quiet and die.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "God, I have two requests, then I can face you.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Stop beating me, [^72] and stop terrifying me.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then call, and I will answer. Or let me speak, and then answer me.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "What are my sins and iniquities? Show me what have I done wrong; how have I rebelled against you?\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Why are you unfriendly towards me?[^73] Why do you treat me as your enemy?\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Would you frighten a leaf blown by the wind or hunt down a piece of straw?\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For you write down bitter things against me and pay me back for the sins of my youth.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You put my feet in the stocks. You keep an eye on every step I take. You even inspect my footprints!\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I'm falling apart like something rotten, like moth-eaten clothes.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}